    26→## 2.1.0
    27→
    28→- Deprecated
    29→  - Instantiating `TOMLDecodeError` with free-form arguments.
    30→    `msg`, `doc` and `pos` arguments should be given.
    31→- Added
    32→  - `msg`, `doc`, `pos`, `lineno` and `colno` attributes to `TOMLDecodeError`
    33→
    34→## 2.0.2
    35→
    36→- Removed
    37→  - Python 3.7 support
    38→- Improved
    39→  - Make `loads` raise `TypeError` not `AttributeError` on bad input types that do not have the `replace` attribute.
    40→    Improve error message when `bytes` is received.
    41→- Type annotations
    42→  - Type annotate `load` input as `typing.IO[bytes]` (previously `typing.BinaryIO`).
    43→
    44→## 2.0.1
    45→
    46→- Improved
    47→  - Make bundling easier by using relative imports internally and adding license and copyright notice to source files.
    48→  - Make error messages more uniform
    49→  - Raise a friendly `TypeError` for wrong file mode
    50→  - Allow `parse_float` to return objects having the `append` attr
    51→  - Eagerly raise an error if `parse_float` returns an illegal type
    52→- Packaging
    53→  - Move from `pytest` testing framework to `unittest` and remove `python-dateutil` test dependency.
    54→    Tests now only require Python interpreter.
    55→
    56→## 1.2.3
    57→
    58→- Fixed
    59→  - Backport: Allow lower case "t" and "z" in datetimes
    60→
    61→## 2.0.0
    62→
    63→- Removed
    64→  - Python 3.6 support
    65→  - Support for text file objects as `load` input. Use binary file objects instead.
    66→  - First argument of `load` and `loads` can no longer be passed by keyword.
    67→- Fixed
    68→  - Allow lower case "t" and "z" in datetimes
    69→- Improved
    70→  - Raise an error when dotted keys define values outside the "current table".
    71→    Technically speaking TOML v1.0.0 does allow such assignments
    72→    but that isn't intended by specification writers,
    73→    and will change in a future specification version (see the [pull request](https://github.com/toml-lang/toml/pull/848)).
    74→
    75→## 1.2.2
    76→
    77→- Fixed
    78→  - Illegal characters in error messages were surrounded by two pairs of quotation marks
    79→- Improved
    80→  - `TOMLDecodeError.__module__` is now the public import path (`tomli`) instead of private import path (`tomli._parser`)
    81→  - Eliminated an import cycle when `typing.TYPE_CHECKING` is `True`.
    82→    This allows `sphinx-autodoc-typehints` to resolve type annotations.
    83→
    84→## 1.2.1
    85→
    86→- Fixed
    87→  - Raise an error if a carriage return (without a following line feed) is found in a multi-line basic string
    88→- Type annotations
    89→  - Type annotate `load` input as `typing.BinaryIO` only to discourage use of deprecated text file objects.
    90→- Packaging
    91→  - Remove legacy `setup.py` from PyPI source distribution.
    92→    If you're a packager and absolutely need this file, please create an issue.
    93→
    94→## 1.2.0
    95→
    96→- Deprecated
    97→  - Text file objects as input to `load`.
    98→    Binary file objects should be used instead to avoid opening a TOML file with universal newlines or with an encoding other than UTF-8.
